Name: AMPERE
OwnedComment: Amps

Name: CELSIUS
OwnedComment: Degrees Celsius

Name: COUNT
OwnedComment: A count of something.

Name: DECIBEL
OwnedComment: Sound Level

Name: DEGREE
OwnedComment: Angle in degrees

Name: DEGREE/SECOND
OwnedComment: Angular degrees per second

Name: DEGREE/SECOND^2
OwnedComment: Angular acceleration in degrees per second squared

Name: HERTZ
OwnedComment: Frequency measured in cycles per second

Name: JOULE
OwnedComment: A measurement of energy.

Name: KILOGRAM
OwnedComment: Kilograms

Name: LITER
OwnedComment: Measurement of volume of a fluid

Name: LITER/SECOND
OwnedComment: Liters per second

Name: MICRO_RADIAN
OwnedComment: Measurement of Tilt

Name: MILLIMETER
OwnedComment: Millimeters

Name: MILLIMETER_3D
OwnedComment: A point in space identified by X, Y, and Z positions and represented by a space-delimited set of numbers each expressed in millimeters.

Name: MILLIMETER/REVOLUTION
OwnedComment: Millimeters per revolution.

Name: MILLIMETER/SECOND
OwnedComment: Millimeters per second

Name: MILLIMETER/SECOND^2
OwnedComment: Acceleration in millimeters per second squared

Name: NEWTON
OwnedComment: Force in Newtons

Name: NEWTON_METER
OwnedComment: Torque, a unit for force times distance.

Name: OHM
OwnedComment: Measure of Electrical Resistance

Name: PASCAL
OwnedComment: Pressure in Newtons per square meter

Name: PASCAL_SECOND
OwnedComment: Measurement of Viscosity

Name: PERCENT
OwnedComment: Percentage

Name: PH
OwnedComment: A measure of the acidity or alkalinity of a solution.

Name: REVOLUTION/MINUTE
OwnedComment: Revolutions per minute

Name: SECOND
OwnedComment: A measurement of time.

Name: SIEMENS/METER
OwnedComment: A measurement of Electrical Conductivity

Name: VOLT
OwnedComment: Volts

Name: VOLT_AMPERE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the apparent power in an electrical circuit, equal to the product of root-mean-square (RMS) voltage and RMS current (commonly referred to as VA).

Name: VOLT_AMPERE_REACTIVE
OwnedComment: The measurement of reactive power in an AC electrical circuit (commonly referred to as VAR).

Name: WATT
OwnedComment: Watts

Name: WATT_SECOND
OwnedComment: Measurement of electrical energy, equal to one Joule

Name: ACCELERATION
OwnedComment: The measurement of the rate of change of velocity.

Name: ACCUMULATED_TIME
OwnedComment: The measurement of accumulated time for an activity or event.

Name: ACTIVE_AXES
OwnedComment: The set of axes currently associated with a {model:Path} or {model:Controller} {term:Structural Element}.

Name: ACTUATOR
OwnedComment:
A mechanism for moving or controlling a mechanical part of a piece of equipment.   
 It takes energy usually provided by air, electric current, or liquid and converts the energy into some kind of motion.

Name: ACTUATOR_STATE
OwnedComment: Represents the operational state of an apparatus for moving or controlling a mechanism or system.

Name: ALARM
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED:* Replaced with {model:CONDITION} category data items in Version 1.1.0.

Name: AMPERAGE
OwnedComment: The measurement of electrical current.

Name: ANGLE
OwnedComment: The measurement of angular position.

Name: ANGULAR_ACCELERATION
OwnedComment: The measurement rate of change of angular velocity.

Name: ANGULAR_VELOCITY
OwnedComment: The measurement of the rate of change of angular position.

Name: ASSET_CHANGED
OwnedComment: The value of the {term:CDATA} for the event *MUST* be the {model:assetId} of the asset that has been added or changed. There will not be a separate message for new assets.

Name: ASSET_REMOVED
OwnedComment: The value of the {term:CDATA} for the event *MUST* be the {model:assetId} of the asset that has been removed. The asset will still be visible if requested with the {model:includeRemoved} parameter as described in the protocol section. When assets are removed they are not moved to the beginning of the most recently modified list.

Name: AVAILABILITY
OwnedComment: Represents the {term:Agent}'s ability to communicate with the data source.

Name: AXIS_COUPLING
OwnedComment:
Describes the way the axes will be associated to each other. 
  
 This is used in conjunction with {model:COUPLED_AXES} to indicate the way they are interacting.

Name: AXIS_FEEDRATE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the feedrate of a linear axis.

Name: AXIS_FEEDRATE_OVERRIDE
OwnedComment: The value of a signal or calculation issued to adjust the feedrate of an individual linear type axis.

Name: AXIS_INTERLOCK
OwnedComment: An indicator of the state of the axis lockout function when power has been removed and the axis is allowed to move freely.

Name: AXIS_STATE
OwnedComment: An indicator of the controlled state of a {model:Linear} or {model:Rotary} component representing an axis.

Name: BLOCK
OwnedComment: The line of code or command being executed by a {model:Controller} {term:Structural Element}.

Name: BLOCK_COUNT
OwnedComment: The total count of the number of blocks of program code that have been executed since execution started.

Name: CAPACITY_FLUID
OwnedComment: The fluid capacity of an object or container.

Name: CAPACITY_SPATIAL
OwnedComment: The geometric capacity of an object or container.

Name: CHUCK_INTERLOCK
OwnedComment: An indication of the state of an interlock function or control logic state intended to prevent the associated {model:CHUCK} component from being operated.

Name: CHUCK_STATE
OwnedComment: An indication of the operating state of a mechanism that holds a part or stock material during a manufacturing process. It may also represent a mechanism that holds any other mechanism in place within a piece of equipment.

Name: CLOCK_TIME
OwnedComment: The value provided by a timing device at a specific point in time.

Name: CLOSE_CHUCK
OwnedComment: Service to close a chuck.

Name: CLOSE_DOOR
OwnedComment: Service to close a door.

Name: CODE
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.1.

Name: COMMUNICATIONS
OwnedComment: An indication that the piece of equipment has experienced a communications failure.

Name: COMPOSITION_STATE
OwnedComment: An indication of the operating condition of a mechanism represented by a {model:Composition} type element.

Name: CONCENTRATION
OwnedComment: The measurement of the percentage of one component within a mixture of components

Name: CONDUCTIVITY
OwnedComment: The measurement of the ability of a material to conduct electricity.

Name: CONTROLLER_MODE
OwnedComment: The current operating mode of the {model:Controller} component.

Name: CONTROLLER_MODE_OVERRIDE
OwnedComment: A setting or operator selection that changes the behavior of a piece of equipment.

Name: COUPLED_AXES
OwnedComment: Refers to the set of associated axes.

Name: CUTTING_SPEED
OwnedComment: The speed difference (relative velocity) between the cutting mechanism and the surface of the workpiece it is operating on.

Name: DATA_RANGE
OwnedComment: An indication that the value of the data associated with a measured value or a calculation is outside of an expected range.

Name: DATE_CODE
OwnedComment:
The time and date code associated with a material or other physical item.
  
 {model:DATE_CODE} *MUST* be reported in ISO 8601 format.

Name: DENSITY
OwnedComment: The volumetric mass of a material per unit volume of that material.

Name: DEPOSITION_ACCELERATION_VOLUMETRIC
OwnedComment: The rate of change in spatial volume of material deposited in an additive manufacturing process.

Name: DEPOSITION_DENSITY
OwnedComment: The density of the material deposited in an additive manufacturing process per unit of volume.

Name: DEPOSITION_MASS
OwnedComment: The mass of the material deposited in an additive manufacturing process.

Name: DEPOSITION_RATE_VOLUMETRIC
OwnedComment: The rate at which a spatial volume of material is deposited in an additive manufacturing process.

Name: DEPOSITION_VOLUME
OwnedComment: The spatial volume of material to be deposited in an additive manufacturing process.

Name: DEVICE_UUID
OwnedComment:
The identifier of another piece of equipment that is temporarily associated with a component of this piece of equipment to perform a particular function.
  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a NMTOKEN XML type.

Name: DIRECTION
OwnedComment: The direction of motion.

Name: DISPLACEMENT
OwnedComment: The measurement of the change in position of an object.

Name: DOOR_STATE
OwnedComment: The operational state of a {model:DOOR} type component or composition element.

Name: ELECTRICAL_ENERGY
OwnedComment: The measurement of electrical energy consumption by a component.

Name: EMERGENCY_STOP
OwnedComment: The current state of the emergency stop signal for a piece of equipment, controller path, or any other component or subsystem of a piece of equipment.

Name: END_OF_BAR
OwnedComment: An indication of whether the end of a piece of bar stock being feed by a bar feeder has been reached.

Name: EQUIPMENT_MODE
OwnedComment: An indication that a piece of equipment, or a sub-part of a piece of equipment, is performing specific types of activities.

Name: EQUIPMENT_TIMER
OwnedComment: The measurement of the amount of time a piece of equipment or a sub-part of a piece of equipment has performed specific activities.

Name: EXECUTION
OwnedComment: The execution status of the {model:Controller}.

Name: FILL_LEVEL
OwnedComment: The measurement of the amount of a substance remaining compared to the planned maximum amount of that substance.

Name: FLOW
OwnedComment: The measurement of the rate of flow of a fluid.

Name: FREQUENCY
OwnedComment: The measurement of the number of occurrences of a repeating event per unit time.

Name: FUNCTIONAL_MODE
OwnedComment: The current intended production status of the device or component.

Name: GLOBAL_POSITION
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.1

Name: HARDNESS
OwnedComment: The measurement of the hardness of a material.

Name: HARDWARE
OwnedComment: An indication of a fault associated with the hardware subsystem of the {term:Structural Element}.

Name: INTERFACE_STATE
OwnedComment: An indication of the operational state of an {model:Interface} component.

Name: LENGTH
OwnedComment: The measurement of the length of an object.

Name: LEVEL
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.2.  See {model:FILL_LEVEL}

Name: LINE
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.4.0.

Name: LINEAR_FORCE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the push or pull introduced by an actuator or exerted on an object.

Name: LINE_LABEL
OwnedComment: An optional identifier for a {model:BLOCK} of code in a {model:PROGRAM}.

Name: LINE_NUMBER
OwnedComment: A reference to the position of a block of program code within a control program.

Name: LOAD
OwnedComment: The measurement of the actual versus the standard rating of a piece of equipment.

Name: LOGIC_PROGRAM
OwnedComment: An indication that an error occurred in the logic program or programmable logic controller (PLC) associated with a piece of equipment.

Name: MASS
OwnedComment: The measurement of the mass of an object(s) or an amount of material.

Name: MATERIAL
OwnedComment: The identifier of a material used or consumed in the manufacturing process.

Name: MATERIAL_CHANGE
OwnedComment: Service to change the type of material or product being loaded or fed to a piece of equipment.

Name: MATERIAL_FEED
OwnedComment: Service to advance material or feed product to a piece of equipment from a continuous or bulk source.

Name: MATERIAL_LAYER
OwnedComment:
Identifies the layers of material applied to a part or product as part of an additive manufacturing process.
  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be an integer.

Name: MATERIAL_LOAD
OwnedComment: Service to load a piece of material or product.

Name: MATERIAL_RETRACT
OwnedComment: Service to remove or retract material or product.

Name: MATERIAL_UNLOAD
OwnedComment: Service to unload a piece of material or product.

Name: MESSAGE
OwnedComment: Any text string of information to be transferred from a piece of equipment to a client software application.

Name: MOTION_PROGRAM
OwnedComment: An indication that an error occurred in the motion program associated with a piece of equipment.

Name: OPEN_CHUCK
OwnedComment: Service to open a chuck.

Name: OPEN_DOOR
OwnedComment: Service to open a door.

Name: OPERATOR_ID
OwnedComment: The identifier of the person currently responsible for operating the piece of equipment.

Name: PALLET_ID
OwnedComment: The identifier for a pallet.

Name: PART_CHANGE
OwnedComment: Service to change the part or product associated with a piece of equipment to a different part or product.

Name: PART_COUNT
OwnedComment: The count of parts produced.

Name: PART_DETECT
OwnedComment:
An indication designating whether a part or work piece has been detected or is present.
  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:PRESENT} or {model:NOT_PRESENT}.

Name: PART_ID
OwnedComment: An identifier of a part in a manufacturing operation.

Name: PART_NUMBER
OwnedComment:
An identifier of a part or product moving through the manufacturing process. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: PATH_FEEDRATE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the feedrate for the axes, or a single axis, associated with a {model:Path} component-a vector.

Name: PATH_FEEDRATE_OVERRIDE
OwnedComment: The value of a signal or calculation issued to adjust the feedrate for the axes associated with a {model:Path} component that may represent a single axis or the coordinated movement of multiple axes.

Name: PATH_FEEDRATE_PER_REVOLUTION
OwnedComment: The feedrate for the axes, or a single axis.

Name: PATH_MODE
OwnedComment: Describes the operational relationship between a {model:Path} {term:Structural Element} and another {model:Path} {term:Structural Element} for pieces of equipment comprised of multiple logical groupings of controlled axes or other logical operations.

Name: PATH_POSITION
OwnedComment: A measured or calculated position of a control point associated with a {model:Controller} element, or {model:Path} element if provided, of a piece of equipment.

Name: PH
OwnedComment: A measure of the acidity or alkalinity of a solution.

Name: POSITION
OwnedComment: A measured or calculated position of a {model:Component} element as reported by a piece of equipment.

Name: POWER_FACTOR
OwnedComment: The measurement of the ratio of real power flowing to a load to the apparent power in that AC circuit.

Name: POWER_STATE
OwnedComment: The indication of the status of the source of energy for a {term:Structural Element} to allow it to perform its intended function or the state of an enabling signal providing permission for the {term:Structural Element} to perform its functions.

Name: POWER_STATUS
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.1.0.

Name: PRESSURE
OwnedComment: The measurement of force per unit area exerted by a gas or liquid.

Name: PROCESS_TIME
OwnedComment:
The time and date associated with an activity or event.
  
 {model:PROCESS_TIME} *MUST* be reported in ISO 8601 format.

Name: PROCESS_TIMER
OwnedComment: The measurement of the amount of time a piece of equipment has performed different types of activities associated with the process being performed at that piece of equipment.

Name: PROGRAM
OwnedComment: The name of the logic or motion program being executed by the {model:Controller} component.

Name: PROGRAM_COMMENT
OwnedComment:
A comment or non-executable statement in the control program.
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: PROGRAM_EDIT
OwnedComment:
An indication of the status of the {model:Controller} components program editing mode. 
 On many controls, a program can be edited while another program is currently being executed.

Name: PROGRAM_EDIT_NAME
OwnedComment:
The name of the program being edited. 
 This is used in conjunction with {model:PROGRAM_EDIT} when in {model:ACTIVE} state. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: PROGRAM_HEADER
OwnedComment: The non-executable header section of the control program.

Name: PROGRAM_LOCATION
OwnedComment: The Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for the source file associated with {model:PROGRAM}.

Name: PROGRAM_LOCATION_TYPE
OwnedComment:
Defines whether the logic or motion program defined by {model:PROGRAM} is being executed from the local memory of the controller or from an outside source.
  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:LOCAL} or {model:EXTERNAL}.

Name: PROGRAM_NEST_LEVEL
OwnedComment:
An indication of the nesting level within a control program that is associated with the code or instructions that is currently being executed.
  
 If an Initial Value is not defined, the nesting level associated with the highest or initial nesting level of the program *MUST* default to zero (0).
  
 The value reported for {model:PROGRAM_NEST_LEVEL} *MUST* be an integer.

Name: RESISTANCE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the degree to which a substance opposes the passage of an electric current.

Name: ROTARY_MODE
OwnedComment: The current operating mode for a {model:Rotary} type axis.

Name: ROTARY_VELOCITY
OwnedComment: The measurement of the rotational speed of a rotary axis.

Name: ROTARY_VELOCITY_OVERRIDE
OwnedComment:
The value of a command issued to adjust the programmed velocity for a {model:Rotary} type axis.
 This command represents a percentage change to the velocity calculated by a logic or motion program or set by a switch for a {model:Rotary} type axis.

Name: SERIAL_NUMBER
OwnedComment: The serial number associated with a {model:Component}, {model:Asset}, or {model:Device}. The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: SOUND_LEVEL
OwnedComment: The measurement of a sound level or sound pressure level relative to atmospheric pressure.

Name: SPINDLE_INTERLOCK
OwnedComment: An indication of the status of the spindle for a piece of equipment when power has been removed and it is free to rotate.

Name: SPINDLE_SPEED
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.2.  Replaced by {model:ROTARY_VELOCITY}

Name: STRAIN
OwnedComment: The measurement of the amount of deformation per unit length of an object when a load is applied.

Name: SYSTEM
OwnedComment: A general purpose indication associated with an electronic component of a piece of equipment or a controller that represents a fault that is not associated with the operator, program, or hardware.

Name: TEMPERATURE
OwnedComment: The measurement of temperature.

Name: TENSION
OwnedComment: The measurement of a force that stretches or elongates an object.

Name: TILT
OwnedComment: The measurement of angular displacement.

Name: TOOL_ASSET_ID
OwnedComment: The identifier of an individual tool asset.The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: TOOL_GROUP
OwnedComment: An identifier for the tool group associated with a specific tool. Commonly used to designate spare tools.

Name: TOOL_ID
OwnedComment: *DEPRECATED* in Version 1.2.0.   See {model:TOOL_ASSET_ID}. *DEPRECATED:The identifier of the tool currently in use for a given {model:Path}.*

Name: TOOL_NUMBER
OwnedComment:
The identifier assigned by the {model:Controller} component to a cutting tool when in use by a piece of equipment. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: TOOL_OFFSET
OwnedComment: A reference to the tool offset variables applied to the active cutting tool associated with a {model:Path} in a {model:Controller} type component.

Name: TORQUE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the turning force exerted on an object or by an object.

Name: USER
OwnedComment: The identifier of the person currently responsible for operating the piece of equipment.

Name: VARIABLE
OwnedComment: A data value whose meaning may change over time due to changes in the opertion of a piece of equipment or the process being executed on that piece of equipment.

Name: VELOCITY
OwnedComment: The measurement of the rate of change of position of a {model:Component}.

Name: VISCOSITY
OwnedComment: The measurement of a fluids resistance to flow.

Name: VOLTAGE
OwnedComment: The measurement of electrical potential between two points.

Name: VOLT_AMPERE
OwnedComment: The measurement of the apparent power in an electrical circuit, equal to the product of root-mean-square (RMS) voltage and RMS current (commonly referred to as VA).

Name: VOLT_AMPERE_REACTIVE
OwnedComment: The measurement of reactive power in an AC electrical circuit (commonly referred to as VAR).

Name: VOLUME_FLUID
OwnedComment: The fluid volume of an object or container.

Name: VOLUME_SPATIAL
OwnedComment: The geometric volume of an object or container.

Name: WAIT_STATE
OwnedComment:
An indication of the reason that {model:EXECUTION} is reporting a value of {model:WAIT}.
  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:POWERING_UP}, {model:POWERING_DOWN}, {model:PART_LOAD}, {model:PART_UNLOAD}, {model:TOOL_LOAD}, {model:TOOL_UNLOAD}, {model:MATERIAL_LOAD}, {model:MATERIAL_UNLOAD}, {model:SECONDARY_PROCESS}, {model:PAUSING}, or {model:RESUMING}.

Name: WATTAGE
OwnedComment: The measurement of power flowing through or dissipated by an electrical circuit or piece of equipment.

Name: WIRE
OwnedComment: A string like piece or filament of relatively rigid or flexible material provided in a variety of diameters.

Name: WORKHOLDING_ID
OwnedComment:
The identifier for the current workholding or part clamp in use by a piece of equipment. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be a text string.

Name: WORK_OFFSET
OwnedComment: A reference to the offset variables for a work piece or part associated with a {model:Path} in a {model:Controller} type component.

Name: ABSOLUTE
OwnedComment: The position of a block of program code relative to the beginning of the control program.

Name: ACTION
OwnedComment:
An indication of the operating state of a mechanism represented by a {model:Composition} type component.
 The operating state indicates whether the {model:Composition} element is activated or disabled. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ACTIVE} or {model:INACTIVE}.

Name: ACTUAL
OwnedComment: The measured value of the data item type given by a sensor or encoder.

Name: ALL
OwnedComment: The count of all the parts produced.  If the subtype is not given, this is the default.

Name: ALTERNATING
OwnedComment: The measurement of alternating voltage or current.   If not specified further in statistic, defaults to RMS voltage.

Name: A_SCALE
OwnedComment: A Scale weighting factor.   This is the default weighting factor if no factor is specified

Name: AUXILIARY
OwnedComment: When multiple locations on a piece of bar stock are referenced as the indication for the {model:END_OF_BAR}, the additional location(s) *MUST* be designated as {model:AUXILIARY} indication(s) for the {model:END_OF_BAR}.

Name: BAD
OwnedComment: Indicates the count of incorrect parts produced.

Name: BRINELL
OwnedComment: A scale to measure the resistance to deformation of a surface.

Name: B_SCALE
OwnedComment: B Scale weighting factor

Name: COMMANDED
OwnedComment: A value specified by the {model:Controller} type component.

Name: CONSUMED
OwnedComment: The amount of bulk material consumed from an object or container during a manufacturing process.

Name: CONTROL
OwnedComment: The state of the enabling signal or control logic that enables or disables the function or operation of the {term:Structural Element}.

Name: C_SCALE
OwnedComment: C Scale weighting factor

Name: DELAY
OwnedComment: A piece of equipment waiting for an event or an action to occur.

Name: DIRECT
OwnedComment: The measurement of DC current or voltage.

Name: DRY_RUN
OwnedComment:
A setting or operator selection used to execute a test mode to confirm the execution of machine functions. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ON} or {model:OFF}. 
 When {model:DRY_RUN} is {model:ON}, the equipment performs all of its normal functions, except no part or product is produced.  If the equipment has a spindle, spindle operation is suspended.

Name: D_SCALE
OwnedComment: D Scale weighting factor

Name: EXPIRATION
OwnedComment: The time and date code relating to the expiration or end of useful life for a material or other physical item.

Name: FIRST_USE
OwnedComment: The time and date code relating the first use of a material or other physical item.

Name: GOOD
OwnedComment: Indicates the count of correct parts made.

Name: INCREMENTAL
OwnedComment: The position of a block of program code relative to the occurrence of the last {model:LINE_LABEL} encountered in the control program.

Name: JOG
OwnedComment: The feedrate specified by a logic or motion program, by a pre-set value, or set by a switch as the feedrate for the {model:Axes}.

Name: LATERAL
OwnedComment:
An indication of the position of a mechanism that may move in a lateral direction.   The mechanism is represented by a {model:Composition} type component. 
 The position information indicates whether the {model:Composition} element is positioned to the right, to the left, or is in transition.  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:RIGHT}, {model:LEFT}, or {model:TRANSITIONING}.

Name: LEEB
OwnedComment: A scale to measure the elasticity of a surface.

Name: LENGTH
OwnedComment: A reference to a length type tool offset variable.

Name: LINE
OwnedComment: The state of the power source for the {term:Structural Element}.

Name: LINEAR
OwnedComment: The direction of motion of a linear motion.

Name: LOADED
OwnedComment: Subparts of a piece of equipment are under load.

Name: MACHINE_AXIS_LOCK
OwnedComment:
A setting or operator selection that changes the behavior of the controller on a piece of equipment. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ON} or {model:OFF}. 
 When {model:MACHINE_AXIS_LOCK} is {model:ON}, program execution continues normally, but no equipment motion occurs

Name: MAIN
OwnedComment: The identity of the primary logic or motion program currently being executed. It is the starting nest level in a call structure and may contain calls to sub programs.

Name: MAINTENANCE
OwnedComment: Action related to maintenance on the piece of equipment.

Name: MANUAL_UNCLAMP
OwnedComment:
An indication of the state of an operator controlled interlock that can inhibit the ability to initiate an unclamp action of an electronically controlled chuck.
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ACTIVE} or {model:INACTIVE}. 
 When {model:MANUAL_UNCLAMP} is {model:ACTIVE}, it is expected that a chuck cannot be unclamped until {model:MANUAL_UNCLAMP} is set to {model:INACTIVE}.

Name: MANUFACTURE
OwnedComment: The time and date code relating to the production of a material or other physical item.

Name: MAXIMUM
OwnedComment: Maximum value of a data entity or attribute.

Name: MINIMUM
OwnedComment: The minimum value of a data entity or attribute.

Name: MOHS
OwnedComment: A scale to measure the resistance to scratching of a surface.

Name: MOTION
OwnedComment:
An indication of the open or closed state of a mechanism.   The mechanism is represented by a {model:Composition} type component. 
 The operating state indicates whether the state of the {model:Composition} element is open, closed, or unlatched.   
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:OPEN}, {model:UNLATCHED}, or {model:CLOSED}.

Name: NO_SCALE
OwnedComment: No weighting factor on the frequency scale

Name: OPERATING
OwnedComment: A piece of equipment are powered or performing any activity.

Name: OPERATOR
OwnedComment: The identifier of the person currently responsible for operating the piece of equipment.

Name: OPTIONAL_STOP
OwnedComment:
A setting or operator selection that changes the behavior of the controller on a piece of equipment. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ON} or {model:OFF}.
 The program execution is stopped after a specific program block is executed when {model:OPTIONAL_STOP} is {model:ON}.    
 In the case of a G-Code program, a program {model:BLOCK} containing a M01 code designates the command for an {model:OPTIONAL_STOP}. 
 {model:EXECUTION} *MUST* change to {model:OPTIONAL_STOP} after a program block specifying an optional stop is executed and the {model:OPTIONAL_STOP} selection is {model:ON}.

Name: OVERRIDE
OwnedComment: The operators overridden value.

Name: POWERED
OwnedComment: Primary  power is  applied  to the  piece  of  equipment and,  as  a minimum, the controller or logic portion of the piece of equipment is powered and functioning or components that are required to remain on are powered.

Name: PRIMARY
OwnedComment:
Specific applications *MAY* reference one or more locations on a piece of bar stock as the indication for the {model:END_OF_BAR}. The main or most important location *MUST* be designated as the {model:PRIMARY} indication for the {model:END_OF_BAR}.   
 If no {model:subType} is specified, {model:PRIMARY} *MUST* be the default {model:END_OF_BAR} indication.

Name: PROBE
OwnedComment: The position provided by a measurement probe.

Name: PROCESS
OwnedComment: The measurement of the time from the beginning of production of a part or product on a piece of equipment until the time that production is complete for that part or product on that piece of equipment.  This includes the time that the piece of equipment is running, producing parts or products, or in the process of producing parts.

Name: PROGRAMMED
OwnedComment: The value of a signal or calculation specified by a logic or motion program or set by a switch.

Name: RADIAL
OwnedComment: A reference to a radial type tool offset variable.

Name: RAPID
OwnedComment: The value of a signal or calculation issued to adjust the feedrate of a component or composition that is operating in a rapid positioning mode.

Name: REMAINING
OwnedComment: Remaining measure of an object or an action.

Name: ROCKWELL
OwnedComment: A scale to measure the resistance to deformation of a surface.

Name: ROTARY
OwnedComment:
The rotational direction of a rotary motion using the right hand rule convention.
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:CLOCKWISE} or {model:COUNTER_CLOCKWISE}.

Name: SCHEDULE
OwnedComment: The identity of a control program that is used to specify the order of execution of other programs.

Name: SET_UP
OwnedComment: The identifier of the person currently responsible for preparing a piece of equipment for production or restoring the piece of equipment to a neutral state after production.

Name: SHORE
OwnedComment: A scale to measure the resistance to deformation of a surface.

Name: SINGLE_BLOCK
OwnedComment:
A setting or operator selection that changes the behavior of the controller on a piece of equipment. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ON} or {model:OFF}.
 Program execution is paused after each {model:BLOCK} of code is executed when {model:SINGLE_BLOCK} is {model:ON}.   
 When {model:SINGLE_BLOCK} is {model:ON}, {model:EXECUTION} *MUST* change to {model:INTERRUPTED} after completion of each {model:BLOCK} of code.

Name: STANDARD
OwnedComment: The standard or original length of an object.

Name: START
OwnedComment: The time and date associated with the beginning of an activity or event.

Name: SWITCHED
OwnedComment:
An indication of the activation state of a mechanism represented by a {model:Composition} type component.
 The activation state indicates whether the {model:Composition} element is activated or not.
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ON} or {model:OFF}.

Name: TARGET
OwnedComment: The desired measure or count for a data item value.

Name: TARGET_COMPLETION
OwnedComment: The projected time and date associated with the end or completion of an activity or event.

Name: TOOL_CHANGE_STOP
OwnedComment:
A setting or operator selection that changes the behavior of the controller on a piece of equipment. 
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:ON} or {model:OFF}. 
 Program execution is paused when a command is executed requesting a cutting tool to be changed. 
 {model:EXECUTION} *MUST* change to {model:INTERRUPTED} after completion of the command requesting a cutting tool to be changed and {model:TOOL_CHANGE_STOP} is {model:ON}.

Name: USEABLE
OwnedComment: The remaining useable length of an object.

Name: VERTICAL
OwnedComment:
An indication of the position of a mechanism that may move in a vertical direction. The mechanism is represented by a {model:Composition} type component. 
 The position information indicates whether the {model:Composition} element is positioned to the top, to the bottom, or is in transition.  
 The {term:Valid Data Value} *MUST* be {model:UP}, {model:DOWN}, or {model:TRANSITIONING}.

Name: VICKERS
OwnedComment: A scale to measure the resistance to deformation of a surface.

Name: WORKING
OwnedComment: A piece of equipment performing any activity, the equipment is active and performing a function under load or not.
